
# --- Secrets: encryption at rest -------------------------------------------
# Secrets the panel stores (the Proxmox token, the session key) are ALWAYS
# encrypted in its database — there is no plaintext mode. This only chooses where
# the encryption key comes from:
#
#   set   -> the key lives OUTSIDE the panel's disk (systemd LoadCredential /
#            systemd-creds, a Docker or Kubernetes secret, a KMS). This is the mode
#            that survives a stolen disk image or a leaked backup.
#   unset -> the panel generates <state_dir>/secret.key (0600), in its own file
#            next to the database. Protects the realistic accident (someone copies
#            just the .sqlite3); does NOT protect against an attacker who can
#            already read the state dir as this user or as root.
#
# HLIDSKJALF_SECRET_KEY=<32-byte urlsafe-base64, or any high-entropy string>
# HLIDSKJALF_SECRET_KEY_FILE=/run/credentials/hlidskjalf.service/secret_key

# --- Secrets: supply any of these from a FILE instead of the environment -----
# Secret managers hand you a file, not an env var — and env vars show up in /proc,
# logs, crash dumps and `docker inspect`. Prefer the _FILE form where you can.
# Every secret below has a _FILE twin:
#
# HLIDSKJALF_PVE_TOKEN_SECRET_FILE=/run/secrets/pve_token
# HLIDSKJALF_SESSION_SECRET_FILE=/run/secrets/session_secret
# HLIDSKJALF_ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH_FILE=/run/secrets/admin_hash
# HLIDSKJALF_SWITCH_PASSWORD_FILE=/run/secrets/switch_password
# HLIDSKJALF_PROMETHEUS_TOKEN_FILE=/run/secrets/prometheus_token
# HLIDSKJALF_PROMETHEUS_PASSWORD_FILE=/run/secrets/prometheus_password
